security: The document's sensitivity lies in potentially revealing operational details or surveillance targets related to the specified address. Sharing location under surveillance could compromise ongoing intelligence activities.
summary: A secret cable from the CIA, referencing a previous communication (LA/MIAMI 29190), identifies an address at 1400 SW 16th Street, Miami, FLA 33145, with the telephone number (305) 858-4406, and includes the designator E2 IMPDET, while also mentioning AMMUR-1 and a numeric identifier, 05645.
summary_one_paragraph: This SECRET cable, dated November 29, 1978, originates from the CIA (referenced as STAFF) and is addressed to PRIORITY DIRECTOR, citing previous communication LA/MIAMI 29190. It identifies a specific location at 1400 SW 16th Street in Miami, Florida, including its phone number (305-858-4406), the designator E2 IMPDET, and mentions AMMUR-1 along with the numeric identifier 05645. The message concludes with 'END OF MESSAGE SECRET'.
title: Cable regarding address in Miami, FLA
